	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://shenglufashion.com/2020/04/10/covid-19-and-u-s-apparel-imports-updated-april-2020/" rel="bookmark">COVID-19 and U.S. Apparel Imports (Updated: April&nbsp;2020)</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p><a href="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="7643" data-permalink="https://shenglufashion.com/2020/04/10/covid-19-and-u-s-apparel-imports-updated-april-2020/1-79/" data-orig-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.jpg" data-orig-size="693,475" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="1" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.jpg?w=693" class="  wp-image-7643 aligncenter" src="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.jpg" alt="1" width="624" height="427" srcset="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.jpg?w=624&amp;h=427 624w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.jpg?w=365&amp;h=250 365w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.jpg?w=300&amp;h=206 300w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.jpg 693w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /><img data-attachment-id="7644" data-permalink="https://shenglufashion.com/2020/04/10/covid-19-and-u-s-apparel-imports-updated-april-2020/1-2-3/" data-orig-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.2.jpg" data-orig-size="690,477" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="1.2" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.2.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.2.jpg?w=690" class="  wp-image-7644 aligncenter" src="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.2.jpg" alt="1.2" width="587" height="406" srcset="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.2.jpg?w=587&amp;h=406 587w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.2.jpg?w=362&amp;h=250 362w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.2.jpg?w=300&amp;h=207 300w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/1.2.jpg 690w" sizes="(max-width: 587px) 85vw, 587px" /></a></p>
<p><strong>The spread of the coronavirus (COVID-19) has already resulted in a plummet of U.S. apparel imports that we have never seen in history. </strong>According to latest statistics from the <a href="http://otexa.trade.gov">Office of Textiles and Apparel (OTEXA)</a> under the U.S. Department of Commerce, as of February 2020:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>The value of U.S. apparel imports sharply decreased by 11.2% in February 2020 from a year earlier.</strong> Between January and February 2020, the amount of U.S. apparel imports decreased by 10.9% year over year, which is nearly the same loss as in the 2008-2009 global financial crisis.</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/5.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="7645" data-permalink="https://shenglufashion.com/2020/04/10/covid-19-and-u-s-apparel-imports-updated-april-2020/5-24/" data-orig-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/5.jpg" data-orig-size="636,383" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="5" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/5.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/5.jpg?w=636" class="  wp-image-7645 aligncenter" src="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/5.jpg" alt="5" width="556" height="335" srcset="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/5.jpg?w=556&amp;h=335 556w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/5.jpg?w=415&amp;h=250 415w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/5.jpg?w=300&amp;h=181 300w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/5.jpg 636w" sizes="(max-width: 556px) 85vw, 556px" /></a></p>
<ul>
<li>As the first country took a hit by COVID-19, <strong>China’s apparel exports to the United States nearly collapsed in February 2020&#8211;down as much as 46.1% compared with a year ago </strong>(and -40.6% drop YTD). This result is also worse than the <a href="http://www.miit.gov.cn/n1146312/n1146904/n1648366/n1648368/c7845624/content.html">official Chinese statistics</a>, which reported an overall 20% drop in China’s apparel exports in the first two months of 2020).</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/2.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="7646" data-permalink="https://shenglufashion.com/2020/04/10/covid-19-and-u-s-apparel-imports-updated-april-2020/2-81/" data-orig-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/2.jpg" data-orig-size="702,432" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="2" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/2.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/2.jpg?w=702" class="  wp-image-7646 aligncenter" src="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/2.jpg" alt="2" width="564" height="347" srcset="https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/2.jpg?w=564&amp;h=347 564w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/2.jpg?w=406&amp;h=250 406w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/2.jpg?w=300&amp;h=185 300w, https://shenglufashion.files.wordpress.com/2020/04/2.jpg 702w" sizes="(max-width: 564px) 85vw, 564px" /></a></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>China’s market shares in the U.S. apparel import market dropped to 21.3% in February 2020, a new record low in history</strong> (was 30% in 2019 and 23.9% in January 2020). However, it is important to note that such a downward trend started in October 2019, as U.S. fashion brands and retailers were eager to reduce their exposure to sourcing from China.</li>
<li><strong>China’s lost market shares have been picked up mostly by other Asian suppliers</strong>, particularly Vietnam (18.8% YTD in 2020 vs. 16.2% in 2019) and Bangladesh (9.1% YTD in 2020 vs.7.1% in 2019). <strong>However, there is no clear evidence suggesting that U.S. fashion brands and retailers are giving more apparel sourcing orders to suppliers from the Western Hemisphere</strong>. In the first two months of 2020, only 9.5% of U.S. apparel imports came from CAFTA-DR members (down from 10.3% in 2019) and 4.2% from NAFTA members (down from 4.5% in 2019).</li>
</ul>
